Problem: Rearrange Array Elements by Sign
Topic: Arrays
Difficulty: Medium
Approach:
Create a result array and use two pointers for even and odd indices. Place positive numbers at even indices and negative numbers at odd indices while traversing the original array.
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
vector<int> rearrangeArray(vector<int>& nums) {
    int n = nums.size();
    vector<int> result(n);

    int pos = 0;  // even index
    int neg = 1;  // odd index

    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
        if(nums[i] > 0){
            result[pos] = nums[i];
            pos += 2;
        } else {
            result[neg] = nums[i];
            neg += 2;
        }
    }

    return result;
}
};
